1. ArchiveIndexTool: command-line tool for combining multiple indices 
into a Master file, see Manual, ch. 5.1

usage: ArchiveIndexTool [Options] <archive list file> <output index>

2. ArchiveIndexMakeConfig: a Perl script that generates 
a config file for the ArchiveIndexTool based on a DTD 
and a list of index files (see Manual, ch. 5.1.1)

usage: ArchiveIndexMakeConfig [-d DTD] index {index}

